<content type="xhtml" xml:lang="en-US" xml:base="http://manhattanmarketingmaven.blogs.com/mmm/">
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font size="3"></font><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">The practice of public relations, especially media relations, is making a transition from semi-traditional press agentry to the digital age. In working with both PR agencies and clients, it is clear that the recession will further complicate the process of getting attention and visibility for brands. <o:p></o:p></span></p>
